        {
            "id": "https://rudytrnka.com/groovy-city.html",
            "url": "https://rudytrnka.com/groovy-city.html",
            "title": "Groovy City",
            "summary": "There are a few thing I love to draw and silly, funky,&hellip;",
            "content_html": "<div class=\"gallery-wrapper\"><div class=\"gallery\" data-is-empty=\"false\" data-translation=\"Add images\" data-columns=\"3\">\n<figure class=\"gallery__item\"><a href=\"https://rudytrnka.com/media/posts/22/gallery/20251106_055759.jpg\" data-size=\"4032x3024\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://rudytrnka.com/media/posts/22/gallery/20251106_055759-thumbnail.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"768\" height=\"576\"></a></figure>\n<figure class=\"gallery__item\"><a href=\"https://rudytrnka.com/media/posts/22/gallery/ComfyUI_00631_.png\" data-size=\"1656x1240\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://rudytrnka.com/media/posts/22/gallery/ComfyUI_00631_-thumbnail.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"768\" height=\"575\"></a></figure>\n<figure class=\"gallery__item\"><a href=\"https://rudytrnka.com/media/posts/22/gallery/ComfyUI_00630_.png\" data-size=\"1656x1240\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://rudytrnka.com/media/posts/22/gallery/ComfyUI_00630_-thumbnail.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"768\" height=\"575\"></a></figure>\n</div></div>\n<p>There are a few thing I love to draw and silly, funky, groovy cities is one of them. this was a rough idea for a city that featured basic shapes to convey a fun playful city. Sometimes I like to lightly draw an idea and then use a marker or something with a thicker line weight to see the concept from a distance, stepping back and imagining the concept from a distance sometimes I can see a direction to further the concept. For the AI image made from this sketch the first thing that came to mind was something whimsical to drive home the concept of a magical fun city.</p>",
            "image": "https://rudytrnka.com/media/posts/22/ComfyUI_00631_.png",
            "author": {
                "name": "Rudy"
            },
            "tags": [
                   "Sketch",
                   "Rough Sketch",
                   "AI Image"
            ],
            "date_published": "2026-07-05T19:35:36-04:00",
            "date_modified": "2026-07-05T19:35:36-04:00"
        },
        {
            "id": "https://rudytrnka.com/perspective-is-relative.html",
            "url": "https://rudytrnka.com/perspective-is-relative.html",
            "title": "Perspective is Relative",
            "summary": "This was a surreal sketch using elements to show the concept of&hellip;",
            "content_html": "<div class=\"gallery-wrapper\"><div class=\"gallery\" data-is-empty=\"false\" data-translation=\"Add images\" data-columns=\"2\">\n<figure class=\"gallery__item\"><a href=\"https://rudytrnka.com/media/posts/21/gallery/ComfyUI_00448_.png\" data-size=\"1224x1688\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://rudytrnka.com/media/posts/21/gallery/ComfyUI_00448_-thumbnail.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"768\" height=\"1059\"></a></figure>\n<figure class=\"gallery__item\"><a href=\"https://rudytrnka.com/media/posts/21/gallery/scan0032.jpg\" data-size=\"1653x2181\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://rudytrnka.com/media/posts/21/gallery/scan0032-thumbnail.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"768\" height=\"1013\"></a></figure>\n</div></div>\n<p>This was a surreal sketch using elements to show the concept of perspective is relative. It is meant to be playful but also to show how context is everything. I used AI with this piece to see if could understand my description of the elements and apply the correct coloring and highlights to further convey the concept.</p>",
            "image": "https://rudytrnka.com/media/posts/21/ComfyUI_00448_.png",
            "author": {
                "name": "Rudy"
            },
            "tags": [
                   "Sketch",
                   "AI Image"
            ],
            "date_published": "2026-07-05T19:25:18-04:00",
            "date_modified": "2026-07-05T19:25:18-04:00"
        },
        {
            "id": "https://rudytrnka.com/girl-with-flowers.html",
            "url": "https://rudytrnka.com/girl-with-flowers.html",
            "title": "Girl with Flowers",
            "summary": "I worked at a gas station and the owner did not mind&hellip;",
            "content_html": "<div class=\"gallery-wrapper\"><div class=\"gallery\" data-is-empty=\"false\" data-translation=\"Add images\" data-columns=\"2\">\n<figure class=\"gallery__item\"><a href=\"https://rudytrnka.com/media/posts/20/gallery/ComfyUI_00446_.png\" data-size=\"1224x1688\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://rudytrnka.com/media/posts/20/gallery/ComfyUI_00446_-thumbnail.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"768\" height=\"1059\"></a></figure>\n<figure class=\"gallery__item\"><a href=\"https://rudytrnka.com/media/posts/20/gallery/scan0029.jpg\" data-size=\"1341x1737\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://rudytrnka.com/media/posts/20/gallery/scan0029-thumbnail.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"768\" height=\"995\"></a></figure>\n</div></div>\n<p>I worked at a gas station and the owner did not mind if I drew while at work so long as all my duties were done by the end of my shift. I don't recall what my inspiration was for this one other then recalling where I created it which was as a clerk inside a gas station store. I was interested to see how AI would fill the scene and following my instructions to make the sketch a finished artwork.</p>",
            "image": "https://rudytrnka.com/media/posts/20/ComfyUI_00446_.png",
            "author": {
                "name": "Rudy"
            },
            "tags": [
                   "Sketch",
                   "AI Image"
            ],
            "date_published": "2026-07-05T19:09:37-04:00",
            "date_modified": "2026-07-05T19:09:37-04:00"
        },
        {
            "id": "https://rudytrnka.com/vehicle-fabrication.html",
            "url": "https://rudytrnka.com/vehicle-fabrication.html",
            "title": "Vehicle Fabrication",
            "summary": "I grew up on Long Island watching a family of brothers create&hellip;",
            "content_html": "<p>I grew up on Long Island watching a family of brothers create art of different mediums. One brother was into vehicle fabrication and this was my effort later in life to create my own one a kind custom vehicle. It started after I was hit in the front of the truck ruining the bumper and after looking at prices to replace the bumper, even from a junk yard, I decided to see what custom body kits were available in the market for my ford ranger. The body kit i bought was actually for a different year with a slightly different front end but i figured i could make it work. Well the kit said ready to install but that was misleading, it had not mounting kit or anything to even mount with. This lead to the beginning of fabricating parts to make this vision come to life. The first version of my concept was to blend the body kit into the space that was void since this kit was made for a different ranger. This was the first complete vision. In this pic you will see I went all in adding BMW M3 mirrors and grafting a cobra Shelby hood scoop to the hood.</p>\n<figure class=\"post__image\"><img loading=\"lazy\"  src=\"https://rudytrnka.com/media/posts/19/Picture-018.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"2272\" height=\"1704\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" srcset=\"https://rudytrnka.com/media/posts/19/responsive/Picture-018-xs.jpg 300w ,https://rudytrnka.com/media/posts/19/responsive/Picture-018-sm.jpg 480w ,https://rudytrnka.com/media/posts/19/responsive/Picture-018-md.jpg 768w ,https://rudytrnka.com/media/posts/19/responsive/Picture-018-lg.jpg 1024w\"></figure>\n<p>I filled the bottom space with a grill i had from my jeep Cherokee. And was close to done at this point conceptual, but I saw the grill of the Chrysler 300 and knew it would give the front end the look i was going for, so back to the drawing board.</p>\n<figure class=\"post__image\"><img loading=\"lazy\"  src=\"https://rudytrnka.com/media/posts/19/ranger-300-005.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"2576\" height=\"1932\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" srcset=\"https://rudytrnka.com/media/posts/19/responsive/ranger-300-005-xs.jpg 300w ,https://rudytrnka.com/media/posts/19/responsive/ranger-300-005-sm.jpg 480w ,https://rudytrnka.com/media/posts/19/responsive/ranger-300-005-md.jpg 768w ,https://rudytrnka.com/media/posts/19/responsive/ranger-300-005-lg.jpg 1024w\"></figure>\n<p>Here you see me building up the layers of fiberglass building around the grill of a Chrysler 300. Which brings us to the day I get to paint my finished creation. This photo was taken after the paint dried and I removed the paper like opening a Christmas present.</p>\n<figure class=\"post__image\"><img loading=\"lazy\"  src=\"https://rudytrnka.com/media/posts/19/Photo-0194-2.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1152\" height=\"864\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" srcset=\"https://rudytrnka.com/media/posts/19/responsive/Photo-0194-2-xs.jpg 300w ,https://rudytrnka.com/media/posts/19/responsive/Photo-0194-2-sm.jpg 480w ,https://rudytrnka.com/media/posts/19/responsive/Photo-0194-2-md.jpg 768w ,https://rudytrnka.com/media/posts/19/responsive/Photo-0194-2-lg.jpg 1024w\"></figure>\n<p>below gallery shows the rest of the fabrication i had to complete to convert a body kit for a 2 door into a 4 door body kit as well as the painting : )</p>\n<div class=\"gallery-wrapper\"><div class=\"gallery\" data-is-empty=\"false\" data-translation=\"Add images\" data-columns=\"3\">\n<figure class=\"gallery__item\"><a href=\"https://rudytrnka.com/media/posts/19/gallery/Photo-0004.jpg\" data-size=\"1280x1024\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://rudytrnka.com/media/posts/19/gallery/Photo-0004-thumbnail.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"768\" height=\"614\"></a></figure>\n<figure class=\"gallery__item\"><a href=\"https://rudytrnka.com/media/posts/19/gallery/Photo-0006.jpg\" data-size=\"1280x1024\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://rudytrnka.com/media/posts/19/gallery/Photo-0006-thumbnail.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"768\" height=\"614\"></a></figure>\n<figure class=\"gallery__item\"><a href=\"https://rudytrnka.com/media/posts/19/gallery/Photo-0183.jpg\" data-size=\"1152x864\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://rudytrnka.com/media/posts/19/gallery/Photo-0183-thumbnail.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"768\" height=\"576\"></a></figure>\n<figure class=\"gallery__item\"><a href=\"https://rudytrnka.com/media/posts/19/gallery/test-008.jpg\" data-size=\"2608x1952\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://rudytrnka.com/media/posts/19/gallery/test-008-thumbnail.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"768\" height=\"575\"></a></figure>\n<figure class=\"gallery__item\"><a href=\"https://rudytrnka.com/media/posts/19/gallery/downloadfile.jpg\" data-size=\"800x600\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://rudytrnka.com/media/posts/19/gallery/downloadfile-thumbnail.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"768\" height=\"576\"></a></figure>\n<figure class=\"gallery__item\"><a href=\"https://rudytrnka.com/media/posts/19/gallery/Photo-0189.jpg\" data-size=\"864x1152\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://rudytrnka.com/media/posts/19/gallery/Photo-0189-thumbnail.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"768\" height=\"1024\"></a></figure>\n<figure class=\"gallery__item\"><a href=\"https://rudytrnka.com/media/posts/19/gallery/Photo-0190.jpg\" data-size=\"864x1152\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://rudytrnka.com/media/posts/19/gallery/Photo-0190-thumbnail.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"768\" height=\"1024\"></a></figure>\n<figure class=\"gallery__item\"><a href=\"https://rudytrnka.com/media/posts/19/gallery/Photo-0192.jpg\" data-size=\"864x1152\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://rudytrnka.com/media/posts/19/gallery/Photo-0192-thumbnail.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"768\" height=\"1024\"></a></figure>\n<figure class=\"gallery__item\"><a href=\"https://rudytrnka.com/media/posts/19/gallery/ranger-300-006.jpg\" data-size=\"2576x1932\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://rudytrnka.com/media/posts/19/gallery/ranger-300-006-thumbnail.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"768\" height=\"576\"></a></figure>\n<figure class=\"gallery__item\"><a href=\"https://rudytrnka.com/media/posts/19/gallery/Picture-020.jpg\" data-size=\"2272x1704\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://rudytrnka.com/media/posts/19/gallery/Picture-020-thumbnail.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"768\" height=\"576\"></a></figure>\n</div></div>",
            "image": "https://rudytrnka.com/media/posts/19/Photo-0194.jpg",
            "author": {
                "name": "Rudy"
            },
            "tags": [
                   "Vehicle Fabrication"
            ],
